Two sales representatives of a jewelery shop, Innocent Erim and Emmanuel Ndukwe, were yesterday arraigned before a Lagos Magistrate’s Court sitting in Igbosere, for allegedly stealing 2,000 pieces of rings worth N10 million from their employer and displayed it online.<img class="size-full wp-image-1243908 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=640%2C355&#038;ssl=1" alt="Police" width="640" height="355" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?w=740&amp;ssl=1 740w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=300%2C166&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=260%2C144&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=200%2C111&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Nigeria-Police-Force.jpg?resize=560%2C310&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Erim, 27, and Ndukwe, 29, whose residential addresses were not given, are facing a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing preferred against them by the Police. The prosecutor, Corporal Godspower Ehizoba, told the court that the defendants conspired among themselves to commit the offence. He said the incident took place between February 2017 and March 2019, while they were employees of the shop. Ehizoba said the duo committed the offence at Shop 6, Estate Mall, Femi Okunnu Jakande Round About, Lekki Phase 3, Lagos. The prosecutor said the rings that were stolen belong to the complainant, one Sherifat Mohammed. Taraba Police killings: Army captain engaged welder to remove police cuffs — Findings(Opens in a new browser tab) He said: “When the matter was reported to the Bar Beach Police Station, the defendants were arrested and 119 pieces of the rings were recovered from the defendants. “The complainant was not satisfied with the investigation, she then wrote a petition to Area A, Command, Lion Building Police Station, in Lagos Island, and 1,500 pieces was recovered. “Before the petition, one of the defendants was discovered to have been displaying the rings online. Magistrate K. K. Awoyinka, adjourned the case until September 11, for mention. Vanguard The Police, yesterday, arraigned two sales representatives, Benjamin Chinweike and Emmanuel Idowu, before an Igbosere Magistrate’s Court in Lagos for allegedly obtaining pharmaceutical products worth five million Naira. June 6, 2018 In "Crime Alert" Lagos- A Sales representative, Ekene Ejikeme, 22, who allegedly absconded six years ago after stealing cash and goods valued at N1.8million from his employer was yesterday arraigned before a Lagos Magistrate's Court in Lagos. December 20, 2016 In "News" Three crew members of a ship, who allegedly stole 8000 litres of petroleum products worth N8.4 million, were yesterday arraigned before a Lagos Magistrate’s Court, sitting in Igbosere. July 23, 2019 In "News"